, but to open up a space in which social and political values could be imaginatively re-created, examined, and critiqued. Seeing Double depicts Alexandrian poetry in its proper context-within the writing of foundation stories and within the imaginative redefinition of Egypt as "Two Lands"-no longer the lands of Upper and Lower Egypt, but of a shared Greek and Egyptian culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aComparative literaturexEgyptian and Greek. 0aComparative literaturexGreek and Egyptian. 0aEgyptian poetryxHistory and criticismxEgyptxAlexandria. 0aEgyptian poetryzEgyptzAlexandriaxHistory and criticism. 0aGreek poetry, HellenisticxHistory and criticismxEgyptxAlexandria. 0aGreek poetry, HellenisticzEgyptzAlexandriaxHistory and criticism. 0aLanguage and culturexEgyptxAlexandria. 0aLanguage and culturezEgyptzAlexandria. 0aPoeticsxHistoryxTo 500. 0aPoeticsxHistoryyTo 500. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520927384.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles